In a large mixing bowl, slightly beat the eggs. Stir in corn syrup, sugar, and vanilla. Mix well. Lightly stir in pecans, till well-coated with egg mixture. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 20 minutes. Turn the oven down to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C), and bake for another 30 minutes. Cool before serving. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.